laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: Laboratory examination for polymorphonuclear leukocytes and gram negative rods
laboratory_examinations.findings: 2+ (1-5 per 1000X FIELD): POLYMORPHONUCLEAR LEUKOCYTES. 2+ (1-5 per 1000X FIELD): GRAM NEGATIVE ROD(S).

The appendix is fluid filled and dilated, measuring 1.3 cm, with a hyperenhancing wall. Moderate amount of intraperitoneal and pelvic free fluid with enhancement of the peritoneum in the right lower quadrant. No extraluminal air or discontinuity of the appendix wall to suggest perforation.
